 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6475979658787575`*^9, 3.6475981055552588`*^9}, {
   3.647598193701496*^9, 3.6475982291644692`*^9}, {3.647598266667029*^9, 
   3.6475982828441253`*^9}, {3.6475985073292866`*^9, 3.6475986649342766`*^9}, 
   3.6475987525243154`*^9, 3.647598831152008*^9, {3.6475988863156548`*^9, 
   3.647598927991987*^9}, {3.647599310234209*^9, 3.647599314430582*^9}, {
   3.6475994708851795`*^9, 3.6475994916534433`*^9}, {3.647599523580239*^9, 
   3.647599574993704*^9}, {3.6621293513000402`*^9, 3.662129351367087*^9}, 
   3.668926164386565*^9}],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[
 CounterBox["NumberedFigure"],
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[".",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Several collections of TES waveforms resulting from pulses with particular \
mean photon numbers given by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    OverscriptBox["N", "-"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ", from ",
 "[",
 
 CounterBox["Reference", "RefBoulder"],
 "]."
}], "NumberedFigureCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647600062635156*^9, 3.647600129910725*^9}, {
   3.6476001709076624`*^9, 3.6476001734348464`*^9}, {3.650016141860682*^9, 
   3.650016144099175*^9}, {3.650016175603323*^9, 3.6500161785632963`*^9}, {
   3.661466299488579*^9, 3.661466310775609*^9}, 3.662129434685664*^9, {
   3.662313312502606*^9, 3.662313320246057*^9}, 3.662329547103421*^9, 
   3.6657845453146973`*^9},
 CellTags->"FigBoulderWaveforms"],

Cell["\<\
The goal of PIKA is to characterize individual TES waveforms by the integer \
photon numbers of the pulses that cause them. The photon numbers of \
individual pulses cannot be determined directly; we can only estimate the \
average photon number of all of the pulses, based on the nominal laser and \
attenuator parameters of the light source.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647599408553979*^9, 3.6475994132087493`*^9}, 
   3.6476002785605917`*^9, {3.650016236787736*^9, 3.65001623976363*^9}, {
   3.650016275267509*^9, 3.650016294563672*^9}, {3.6500163295080338`*^9, 
   3.650016337907887*^9}, 3.662242399397606*^9, 3.665787910149729*^9, 
   3.665788012953683*^9}],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "-means clustering, upon which PIKA is based, is a fundamental part of \
unsupervised machine learning. PIKA extends the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "-means algorithm to scenarios in which the ideal distribution that the \
clusters should follow is known, and though some of the implementation is \
specific to the context of TES calibration (e.g. the use of the Poisson \
distribution, the idea of ordering observations by photon number), much of it \
can be generalized without much difficulty to other situations with known \
probability distributions."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476003498365345`*^9, 3.6476003813015327`*^9}, {
   3.6476006884123497`*^9, 3.647600693999114*^9}, {3.6476007863455667`*^9, 
   3.647600914398746*^9}, {3.647601037849555*^9, 3.6476010404547377`*^9}, {
   3.647601143899475*^9, 3.6476012783626137`*^9}, {3.647601476492944*^9, 
   3.647601500304392*^9}, 3.650023255887372*^9, {3.662323284248365*^9, 
   3.6623232893523817`*^9}, 3.665784580960566*^9}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 
 CounterBox["Section"],
 ".",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection"],
 ". ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "-means",
 " Clustering and the Poisson Distribution"
}], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647358487140662*^9, 3.647358512911697*^9}, {
   3.6476015185914745`*^9, 3.6476015201514645`*^9}, 3.6621293514045057`*^9, 
   3.662323305106023*^9}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Traditional ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "-means clustering consists of taking some amount of data and organizing it \
into clusters that minimize their members\[CloseCurlyQuote] distance from the \
cluster mean. Essentially this is a minimization of an objective function, \
the sum over each piece of data of its deviation from its cluster mean (where \
deviation is measured by some relevant definition of distance). We can use a \
similar approach by considering each signal as a high-dimensional vector and \
its deviation from some mean as squared Euclidean distance. Then the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "-means component of the objective function becomes"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.647601535612965*^9, {3.6476020777600913`*^9, 3.6476020952399793`*^9}, {
   3.650016443876687*^9, 3.650016486004591*^9}, {3.662323313950811*^9, 
   3.662323325055073*^9}, {3.665784606521833*^9, 3.665784626168428*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["O", "K"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
      RowBox[{"n", "=", 
       SubscriptBox["n", "0"]}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["n", "0"], "+", "K", "-", "1"}]], 
     RowBox[{
      UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
       RowBox[{"i", "\[Element]", 
        SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}]], 
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["1", 
        SubscriptBox["N", "t"]], 
       RowBox[{
        UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", "t"], 
        SuperscriptBox[
         RowBox[{"[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{
            SubscriptBox["V", "i"], "(", "t", ")"}], "-", 
           RowBox[{
            SubscriptBox[
             OverscriptBox["V", "-"], "n"], "(", "t", ")"}]}], "]"}], 
         "2"]}]}]}]}]}], ","}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476015819560685`*^9, 3.6476017023356967`*^9}},
 CellTags->"eqKMeans"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the signal vector for observation ",
 StyleBox["i",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["V", "i"], "(", "t", ")"}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["t", "th"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " element of the vector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      StyleBox["V",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"],
     FontWeight->"Bold"], "n"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the mean of the cluster ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["C", "n"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["N", "t"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the number of time points; ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["n", "0"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["K", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " give the first cluster\[CloseCurlyQuote]s photon number and number of \
clusters, respectively, and are determined by which photon numbers we expect \
to be associated with at least one pulse based on the Poisson distribution. \
More physically, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is an individual waveform and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      StyleBox["V",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"],
     FontWeight->"Bold"], "n"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the average of the waveforms with an assigned photon number ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647601704208685*^9, 3.647601720234782*^9}, {
   3.6476017759112253`*^9, 3.6476018440413885`*^9}, {3.6476018821825447`*^9, 
   3.647602053929044*^9}, {3.6476021680647125`*^9, 3.647602422355883*^9}, {
   3.650016578069612*^9, 3.6500167472070436`*^9}, 3.650016860324986*^9, {
   3.661466464894307*^9, 3.661466466272307*^9}, {3.662129351451088*^9, 
   3.662129351523738*^9}, {3.662313502125291*^9, 3.662313509348447*^9}, {
   3.662313577504601*^9, 3.662313615846468*^9}, {3.662313649268855*^9, 
   3.6623136497805433`*^9}, {3.667307692307138*^9, 3.6673076973880177`*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To account for the Poisson-distributed cluster sizes, we introduce another \
term, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["O", 
     RowBox[{"P", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "C"}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", "ln"}], " ", "\[ScriptCapitalL]"}]}], TraditionalForm]], 
  "Math"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[ScriptCapitalL]", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the likelihood, according to the Poisson distribution, of a group of \
clusters associated with a group of photon numbers having the particular \
sizes that a given clustering asserts that they do, given the mean photon \
number of the ensemble of pulses. The likelihood of a particular sequence of \
photon numbers occurring in an ensemble with mean ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Mu]", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647601704208685*^9, 3.647601720234782*^9}, {
   3.6476017759112253`*^9, 3.6476018440413885`*^9}, {3.6476018821825447`*^9, 
   3.647602053929044*^9}, {3.6476021680647125`*^9, 3.647602422355883*^9}, {
   3.6476025719153247`*^9, 3.647602665809923*^9}, {3.647602697208922*^9, 
   3.64760270221649*^9}, {3.6476028615404687`*^9, 3.647602869030421*^9}, {
   3.661466504651251*^9, 3.661466508882595*^9}, 3.662313657971965*^9, {
   3.6623137144588013`*^9, 3.6623137249245358`*^9}, {3.665784668552656*^9, 
   3.6657846765950193`*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalL]", "P"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     UnderoverscriptBox["\[Product]", 
      RowBox[{"n", "=", 
       SubscriptBox["n", "0"]}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["n", "0"], "+", "K", "-", "1"}]], 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox[
        RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["e", 
          RowBox[{"-", "\[Mu]"}]], 
         SuperscriptBox["\[Mu]", "n"]}], 
        RowBox[{"n", "!"}]], ")"}], 
      SubscriptBox["m", "n"]]}]}], ","}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647602799340267*^9, 3.647602925910056*^9}},
 CellTags->"eqPoisson"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "n"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the number of waveforms in cluster ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ". We also need a combinatorial component, since different photon-number \
sequences can yield the same eventual cluster sizes:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476029436833425`*^9, 3.647603058615602*^9}, {
   3.6500169847954082`*^9, 3.650016989851078*^9}, 3.650017167980379*^9, {
   3.650017255788745*^9, 3.6500172807575073`*^9}, {3.661466533168138*^9, 
   3.661466534404784*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalL]", "C"], "=", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"M", "!"}], 
     RowBox[{
      UnderoverscriptBox["\[Product]", 
       RowBox[{" ", 
        RowBox[{"n", "=", 
         SubscriptBox["n", "0"]}]}], 
       RowBox[{" ", 
        RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox["n", "0"], "+", "K", "-", "1"}]}]], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["m", "n"], "!"}]}]]}], ","}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476030715207195`*^9, 3.6476031367513013`*^9}, {
   3.6476165641227474`*^9, 3.647616564278746*^9}, 3.667144950325951*^9, {
   3.667145022043374*^9, 3.6671450288497047`*^9}},
 CellTags->"eqCombo"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"M", "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[Sum]", 
     SubscriptBox["m", "n"]}]}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ". Then ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalL]", "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalL]", "P"], 
     SubscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalL]", "C"]}]}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ", and the PIKA objective function is"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476031401364794`*^9, 3.6476031816144137`*^9}, {
  3.647616567104328*^9, 3.6476166019479046`*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["O", 
    RowBox[{"K", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "P", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "C"}]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["1", 
      RowBox[{"2", 
       SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "2"]}]], 
     SubscriptBox["O", "K"]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["O", 
      RowBox[{"P", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "C"}]], "."}]}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476031918217487`*^9, 3.6476032365732613`*^9}, {
  3.662322782495227*^9, 3.662322793605392*^9}},
 CellTags->"eqObjFtn"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The constant ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Sigma]", TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " relating the two terms can be estimated from the data, since the",
 " ",
 "objective function is itself the negative log-likelihood of a normal \
distribution. (This also means that minimizing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["O", 
    RowBox[{"K", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "P", "\[InvisibleSpace]", "C"}]], 
   TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is equivalent to maximizing the product of two likelihoods.) PIKA \
minimizes the objective function by moving waveforms to neighboring clusters."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647603248697384*^9, 3.647603269109053*^9}, {
   3.647603306841611*^9, 3.6476034307634172`*^9}, {3.6478822839717054`*^9, 
   3.6478822920876536`*^9}, 3.650017463903651*^9, 3.650018038752932*^9, {
   3.661466701941803*^9, 3.661466702805201*^9}, {3.6623149469512167`*^9, 
   3.6623149896136103`*^9}, {3.662322808625308*^9, 3.662322811904755*^9}, 
   3.662324941129684*^9, 3.662328645827795*^9}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Once the clusters are optimized, each waveform is assigned an effective \
photon number by a linear interpolation between the two closest cluster \
means. First, we find the value ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "i"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " that minimizes the root mean square deviation of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"1", "-", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "i"]}], ")"}], 
     SubscriptBox[
      OverscriptBox[
       StyleBox["V",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], "n"]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "i"], 
     SubscriptBox[
      OverscriptBox[
       StyleBox["V",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], 
      RowBox[{"n", "'"}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["V",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], "n"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["V",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], 
    RowBox[{"n", "'"}]], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " are the closest and second-closest mean waveforms to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ". In practice, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"i", "\[Element]", 
    SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"n", "'"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"n", "\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ". One can easily show that"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647603248697384*^9, 3.647603269109053*^9}, {
  3.647603306841611*^9, 3.6476034307634172`*^9}, {3.64760347871591*^9, 
  3.6476035319939685`*^9}, {3.6476035672889423`*^9, 3.64760376514007*^9}, {
  3.6476039127259245`*^9, 3.6476039357865763`*^9}, {3.6476040458702707`*^9, 
  3.647604212510403*^9}, {3.6500183010787907`*^9, 3.6500183043267717`*^9}, {
  3.65001840488673*^9, 3.650018429558611*^9}, {3.650018493595045*^9, 
  3.65001856499889*^9}, {3.650018622999168*^9, 3.650018632119158*^9}, {
  3.6614667635412827`*^9, 3.6614667641010036`*^9}, {3.6614668268530083`*^9, 
  3.661466859980156*^9}, {3.661466896756548*^9, 3.661466899667941*^9}, {
  3.662207918314229*^9, 3.662207920130209*^9}, {3.662222269368699*^9, 
  3.6622222724964027`*^9}, {3.662222390649922*^9, 3.662222420831702*^9}, {
  3.662315055136087*^9, 3.6623150607781487`*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "i"], "=", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox[
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox[
          StyleBox["V",
           FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], 
         StyleBox["n",
          FontWeight->"Plain"]],
        FontWeight->"Bold"], "-", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["V",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"]}], ")"}], "\[CenterDot]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox[
         StyleBox["V",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], "n"], "-", 
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox[
         StyleBox["V",
          FontWeight->"Bold",
          FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], 
        RowBox[{"n", "'"}]]}], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"||", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["V",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], "n"], "-", 
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["V",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], 
       RowBox[{"n", "'"}]]}], 
     SuperscriptBox["||", "2"]}]]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647603958353032*^9, 3.6476039766119146`*^9}, {
  3.662207889752614*^9, 3.662207901584339*^9}, {3.66222242802149*^9, 
  3.662222443469594*^9}, {3.662315062991404*^9, 3.662315063777265*^9}},
 CellTags->"eqAlpha"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "for each ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ". The effective photon number is then given by"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476040218676248`*^9, 3.6476040392675133`*^9}, {
  3.6476042250859227`*^9, 3.647604236100452*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox["n", "i", 
    RowBox[{"(", "eff", ")"}]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"1", "-", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "i"]}], ")"}], "n"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "i"], 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"n", "'"}], "."}]}]}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476042428708086`*^9, 3.6476042769333906`*^9}, {
   3.662207854233233*^9, 3.662207871128477*^9}, {3.6622224518694763`*^9, 
   3.662222454877553*^9}, 3.662315067507148*^9}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 
 CounterBox["Section"],
 ".",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection"],
 ".",
 " ",
 "Initial Clustering"
}], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647358487140662*^9, 3.647358512911697*^9}, {
   3.6476043451435533`*^9, 3.647604346095147*^9}, 3.662129351563038*^9}],

Cell["\<\
PIKA needs an initial clustering upon which to improve. Random cluster \
assignment is an option, but a better alternative is to give the observations \
a rough order by photon number, so that our initial guess is actually a \
meaningful estimate. This is done via the dot product method: we assign each \
observation an initial effective photon number\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.647604359107464*^9}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["n", "i", 
     RowBox[{"(", "eff", ")"}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox[
      OverscriptBox["N", "-"],
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox[
        OverscriptBox[
         StyleBox["V",
          FontSlant->"Plain"], 
         StyleBox["-",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]],
        FontWeight->"Bold"], "\[CenterDot]", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["V",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], "i"]}], 
      RowBox[{"||", 
       OverscriptBox[
        StyleBox["V",
         FontWeight->"Bold",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], 
       SuperscriptBox["||", "2"]}]]}]}], ","}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476043712013865`*^9, 3.6476043781161423`*^9}, {
  3.6476044371631637`*^9, 3.6476045867426014`*^9}, {3.6476046222725735`*^9, 
  3.6476046322761097`*^9}, {3.6476051225249596`*^9, 3.647605123570153*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox[
    StyleBox["V",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " is the entire ensemble\[CloseCurlyQuote]s mean, not a cluster mean ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["V",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "-"], "n"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ". The initial clusters are sized to fit each observation and conform to the \
Poisson distribution, and the observations are placed in the clusters by \
order of effective photon number."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647605077088051*^9, 3.6476051105714364`*^9}, {
  3.647605143698024*^9, 3.6476051454608126`*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The geometric interpretation of PIKA and the dot product method is a curve \
and a line, respectively, evolving through hyperspace (shown in Figure ",
 
 CounterBox["NumberedFigure", "FigGeoInterp"],
 "). The dot product method projects each observation onto the mean waveform \
vector (a line) and then assumes that photon number scales linearly with \
distance along the mean vector (which is not actually true, but suffices for \
a first guess); that converts distance relative to the mean to photon number \
relative to the mean. PIKA, in contrast, finds a piecewise linear \
approximation of a curve that passes through the cluster means and projects \
each observation onto that. Both essentially measure photon number by \
progress along a one-dimensional path through high-dimensional space."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476052037262855`*^9, 3.647605233311696*^9}, {
   3.6476057866605773`*^9, 3.647605835795863*^9}, {3.650209193809065*^9, 
   3.650209204045473*^9}, 3.650278954380666*^9, {3.6502790370536222`*^9, 
   3.650279064852162*^9}, 3.661466957499464*^9, {3.662129386861451*^9, 
   3.662129387468912*^9}, {3.662318963432096*^9, 3.662318963599547*^9}, 
   3.662318995310112*^9, {3.662319041332416*^9, 3.662319047236532*^9}, 
   3.6673077328514357`*^9}],

