Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[
 CounterBox["NumberedFigure"],
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[".",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " An illustration of the geometric differences between the dot product \
method (green arrow) and PIKA (",
 "blue",
 " curve). The 3D space here stands in for a high-dimensional space."
}], "NumberedFigureCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647605712435053*^9, 3.64760578160521*^9}, {
   3.6476089923361225`*^9, 3.6476090115943995`*^9}, {3.650018802375072*^9, 
   3.65001885491886*^9}, {3.6502789315959673`*^9, 3.650278933691123*^9}, {
   3.661466988572064*^9, 3.6614669898192377`*^9}, 3.662129351608172*^9, 
   3.662129443629581*^9, {3.662319081435121*^9, 3.6623190821785507`*^9}, {
   3.662319120185652*^9, 3.662319123457343*^9}, {3.665332825940192*^9, 
   3.6653328273159857`*^9}, {3.665336423481802*^9, 3.6653364260799437`*^9}},
 CellTags->"FigGeoInterp"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 
 CounterBox["Section"],
 ".",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection"],
 ".",
 " ",
 "Choice of Mean Photon Number"
}], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647358487140662*^9, 3.647358512911697*^9}, {
   3.647605249211994*^9, 3.6476052533051677`*^9}, {3.647612734221763*^9, 
   3.6476127416937633`*^9}, 3.662129351722636*^9}],

Cell["\<\
PIKA requires knowledge of the ensemble\[CloseCurlyQuote]s mean photon number \
in addition to an initial clustering. There are two ways of supplying that \
knowledge. The first is simply to give the exact mean photon number of the \
incoming pulses, if it is known; then PIKA clusters the data accordingly.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476142887113285`*^9, 3.6476145913653765`*^9}, {
  3.6476146243713765`*^9, 3.6476146861391764`*^9}, {3.6476151378666935`*^9, 
  3.6476151957869225`*^9}, {3.6476152949514875`*^9, 3.64761535071293*^9}, {
  3.6476154288672295`*^9, 3.6476155583735995`*^9}, {3.647617516926633*^9, 
  3.6476175263509727`*^9}, {3.6476175664713154`*^9, 3.647617567076112*^9}, {
  3.647618620589958*^9, 3.647618627472514*^9}, {3.6476186601789045`*^9, 
  3.6476186656564693`*^9}, {3.6476211625189333`*^9, 3.647621162877731*^9}, {
  3.66224302464211*^9, 3.662243026681048*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
The second is to test several mean photon numbers on the data if the true \
mean is not known exactly. The test means should be close together in some \
range around a rough estimate of the true mean; PIKA clusters the data once \
for each value, returning a new (usually better) estimate of the mean based \
on each optimized clustering, as well as the value of the objective function \
associated with each new estimate. (In addition, since the test means are \
close together so that adjacent distributions should be very similar, the \
effective photon numbers for the waveforms from one round are used as the \
initial ordering for the next, instead of the dot product method.)\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476187868884926`*^9, 3.6476188951429987`*^9}, {
  3.6476189646263533`*^9, 3.6476190648071117`*^9}, {3.647621196660514*^9, 
  3.6476212195223675`*^9}, {3.647621284154154*^9, 3.6476213489127383`*^9}, {
  3.647621380761134*^9, 3.647621388592284*^9}, {3.647621791711301*^9, 
  3.6476217969382677`*^9}, {3.6476218336646323`*^9, 3.647621859757665*^9}, {
  3.6622430784169693`*^9, 3.662243094600258*^9}, {3.6623192225376863`*^9, 
  3.6623192411575737`*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The optimized means are usually closer to the true mean than their initial \
seeds, but, depending on the structure of the probability distribution \
underlying the objective function, some optimized means may be moved farther \
away due to attraction to local minima. In the Poisson case, we have observed \
the objective function to have secondary minima at integer differences in \
mean photon number from the primary minimum and convex regions of width 1 \
centered around each minimum. Thus, test means that land in the same region \
as the true mean should be optimized toward the true mean, but those outside \
are diverted by secondary minima. Reference [",
 
 CounterBox["Reference", "RefAtten"],
 "] estimates the range of test means to within half of a photon number from \
the nominal laser power and attenuation."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647619155249132*^9, 3.647619171835826*^9}, 
   3.647619244096763*^9, {3.6476193058788185`*^9, 3.647619338031613*^9}, {
   3.6476193817775326`*^9, 3.647619392182666*^9}, {3.6476194242398605`*^9, 
   3.6476194999091754`*^9}, {3.647619628140354*^9, 3.6476196572013674`*^9}, {
   3.6476197097200313`*^9, 3.6476198285672693`*^9}, {3.6476198694766073`*^9, 
   3.6476199047579813`*^9}, {3.6476212303652983`*^9, 3.647621249916973*^9}, {
   3.6476219369649706`*^9, 3.647621963994997*^9}, {3.662223121891423*^9, 
   3.662223124762311*^9}, {3.6622431161036367`*^9, 3.66224311668764*^9}, 
   3.662319289548274*^9}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 
 CounterBox["Section"],
 ".",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection"],
 ".",
 " ",
 "PIKA\[CloseCurlyQuote]s Results"
}], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.647358487140662*^9, 3.647358512911697*^9}, {
   3.647605249211994*^9, 3.6476052533051677`*^9}, {3.6478702908288097`*^9, 
   3.6478702915932055`*^9}, {3.647870498606279*^9, 3.6478705014610605`*^9}, 
   3.662129351765544*^9}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The following results and images (in Section ",
 
 CounterBox["Section"],
 ".",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection"],
 ") except Figure ",
 
 CounterBox["NumberedFigure", "FigPerf4"],
 " come from [",
 
 CounterBox["Reference", "RefOrigPaper"],
 "]."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476091534576855`*^9, 3.6476091948874197`*^9}, {
   3.6476092492534714`*^9, 3.647609249378271*^9}, {3.6476098538635936`*^9, 
   3.6476098684701*^9}, {3.6476119526347632`*^9, 3.6476119917847633`*^9}, 
   3.647612141931763*^9, {3.661467018211877*^9, 3.66146702415495*^9}, {
   3.662319305942328*^9, 3.6623193061792793`*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Figure ",
 
 CounterBox["NumberedFigure", "FigPerf1"],
 "(a) shows the optimized cluster means from two PIKA runs (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    OverscriptBox["N", "-"], "=", "22.6"}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ", solid red, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    OverscriptBox["N", "-"], "=", "31.6"}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 ", dotted blue). The shapes of the mean waveforms appear independent of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["N", "-"], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 "\[LongDash]reassuring, since the average photon number of an ensemble \
should not affect the shape of individual waveforms. This independence \
indicates that PIKA is properly identifying actual photon numbers in the \
data, and that the average photon number with which it is supplied is not \
unduly affecting the results."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476099368226624`*^9, 3.6476099382578526`*^9}, {
  3.647609976957605*^9, 3.6476101715843544`*^9}, {3.647610208912315*^9, 
  3.6476103182608147`*^9}, {3.661467029507307*^9, 3.661467030114994*^9}, {
  3.661467073395463*^9, 3.661467074050906*^9}, {3.665784748572912*^9, 
  3.665784754179737*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Figure ",
 
 CounterBox["NumberedFigure", "FigPerf1"],
 "(b) is a histogram of the optimized effective photon numbers from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    OverscriptBox["N", "-"], "=", "2.00"}], TraditionalForm]], "Math"],
 " (bin widths of 0.05), which follow a Poisson distribution but with some \
Gaussian spread around the integers (the red curves are Gaussians centered on \
the integers and fitted to the data), resulting in a comb-like shape."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6476103393744793`*^9, 3.6476104235165367`*^9}, {
  3.6476105125519657`*^9, 3.6476105522087116`*^9}, {3.6476105836399107`*^9, 
  3.647610602752788*^9}, {3.647610705217763*^9, 3.6476107444477634`*^9}, {
  3.647610802316763*^9, 3.6476108076277633`*^9}, {3.647610969538763*^9, 
  3.647611102939763*^9}, {3.661467238970359*^9, 3.66146724016157*^9}}],

