 CellTags->"Implementation"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Here we define the functions referenced in the previous section. The \
structure of the following subsections mirrors that of the algorithm skeleton \
above: Subsection ",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection", "ImplOptions"],
 " defines the procedures called before Loop 1 begins, Subsections ",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection", "ImplPreproc"],
 " through ",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection", "ImplOutput"],
 " define those used in Loop 1 (with Subsection ",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection", "ImplOptim"],
 " containing the functions for Loops 2 and 3), and Subsection ",
 
 CounterBox["Subsection", "ImplTimeUsed"],
 " contains the (very minimal) end of the algorithm after exiting Loop 1. The \
functions are defined in the order in which they are called, and each is \
called exactly once. The functions called inside the bodies of these skeleton \
functions (",
 "i.e.",
 " those that take arguments, unlike the functions defined in this section) \
are defined in Sections ",
 
 CounterBox["Section", "ObjFtnUpdate"],
 " and ",
 
 CounterBox["Section", "FunctionDefinitions"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6452798810226398`*^9, 3.64527990985344*^9}, {
