Cell[TextData[{
 "Now we enter Loop 1, whose index, ",
 Cell[BoxData["iNPhotonAvgList"], "MCode"],
 ", is the position in ",
 Cell[BoxData["nPhotonAvgList"], "MCode"],
 " of the current mean photon number. Each iteration of Loop 1 runs PIKA on \
the given dataset with the assumption that the waveforms in the data come \
from pulses incident on the sensor with an average of ",
 Cell[BoxData["nPhotonAvgList"], "MCode"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
  "\[LeftDoubleBracket]", "iNPhotonAvgList", "\[RightDoubleBracket]"}]], 
  "MCode"],
 " photons per pulse. The runs are independent of each other apart from the \
fact that one round\[CloseCurlyQuote]s optimized effective photon numbers are \
used as initial effective photon numbers for the next."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6453533315696383`*^9, 3.6453533344868383`*^9}, {
   3.6453534527560387`*^9, 3.6453534543004384`*^9}, {3.645353500804038*^9, 
